         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Memo. From Bright Brothers &amp; Co. ¶ Flinders Lane West, ¶ Melbourne, ¶  July 29th  ¶ 1872 ¶ To ¶  Baron Von Mueller ¶ Dear Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.07.29</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Bright Brothers &amp; Co.</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: center; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Bombax</seg> sp. (MEL 242390).</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">Memo. From Bright Brothers &amp; Co.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">Flinders Lane West,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">Melbourne,</seg> July 29th <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">1872</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg>To</seg> Baron Von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We shall feel much obliged by your kindly examining the sample of Down herewith which is said to be “Thistle Down” and informing us what it is &amp; where it is grown as we have orders for 20 […] from England.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B B &amp; Co […]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Illegible signature. The file includes an undated follow-up note: ‘My dear Baron | I enclose you a stalk of the so called Thistle down it may throw more light on the matter | Yours truly Reginald Bright’.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
